WEATHER DASHBOARD README

OVERVIEW The Weather Dashboard is a Python-based desktop application that provides real-time weather updates. It uses a graphical interface to help users search for current weather conditions across the globe, featuring a clean layout and automated history tracking.

CORE FEATURES

Real-Time Data: Fetches live temperature, humidity, wind speed, and atmospheric pressure.

Visual Indicators: Uses weather-specific emojis to represent conditions like sunny, rainy, or cloudy.

Search History: Remembers your recent searches and saves them to a local file for future sessions.

Quick Links: Single-click buttons for popular global cities (London, Tokyo, New York, etc.).

Robust Error Handling: Provides clear feedback for incorrect city names or connection issues.

TECHNICAL STACK

Language: Python 

GUI Library: Tkinter

API: OpenWeatherMap (Current Weather Data & Forecast)

Dependencies: 'requests' library for handling API calls.

HOW TO START

Ensure Python is installed on your system.

Install the required library by typing 'pip install requests' in your terminal.

Run the script using the command: 'python <filename>.py'

Enter a city name in the search bar and press Enter or click 'Search'.

FILE MANAGEMENT

weather_history.json: This file is automatically created in your project folder to store your search preferences and history.

API Configuration: The API key and timeout settings are managed within the 'APIConfig' class for easy updates.

USER CONTROLS

Search Bar: Type any city name to fetch data.

Clear History: Resets your saved search list.

Quick Buttons: Click any city name in the bottom panel to refresh data instantly for that location.
